ism and aesthetics? How might we as scholars and creative thinkers further employ the arts to envision and shape a verdant society? Contributors: Carrie Mae Weems, Carmen Gillespie, Rikki Byrd, Amber Lauren Johnson, Doria E. Charlson, Florencia V. Cornet, Daniel McNeil, Lucy Caplan, Genevieve Hyacinthe, Sammantha McCalla, Nettrice R. Gaskins, Abby Dobson, J. Michael Kinsey, Shondrika Moss-Bouldin, Julie B. Johnson, Sharrell D. Luckett, Jasmine Eileen Coles, Tawnya Pettiford-Wates, Rickerby Hinds. Published by Bucknell University Press. Distributed worldwide by Rutgers University Press.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAfrican American artsxPolitical aspects. 0aArts and societyzUnited States. 7aART / General.2bisacsh1 aByrd, Rikki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaplan, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharlson, Doria E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColes, Jasmine Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColes, Jasmine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCornet, Florencia V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobson, Abby, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaskins, Nettrice R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillespie, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinds, Rickerby, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyacinthe, Genevieve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Amber Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Amber, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator